Skyway Aviation Handling Company (SAHCO) Plc has won the 2021 Aviation Handling Company of the Year 2021 in Nigeria. A statement by Vanessa Uansohia, the Manager, Corporate Communications, SAHCO, said that the award was presented to the handling company by ATQnews during its 2022 Travelers Awards, which was held in Abuja, recently. Mr. Ikechi Uko, the organiser of the award commended SAHCO’s doggedness and quality services in the aviation sector. Uko expressed that the nomination was done by stakeholders in the industry based on SAHCO’s contributions to the growth of the aviation and travel sector in the country. “The award was due to SAHCO’s consistent performance in travel business in 2021,” he said. Mr. Basil Agboarumi, Managing Director, SAHCO Plc who received the award on behalf of the company lauded ATQnews for finding SAHCO worthy of the prize. He dedicated the award to God, then to all staff and management of SAHCO PLC for working hard to ensure safe, speedy and efficient aviation ground handling services to clients. SAHCO is the only ground handling company in Nigeria to procure Mobile Cool Dollies which has the capacity to transport temperature sensitive products like pharmaceuticals and other perishables from the aircraft to the warehouse in the same right temperature. POLL At the event, some of SAHCO client airlines won numerous awards, these awardees were from both domestic and international origin, amongst whom were Ibom Air from domestic airlines category and African World Airlines from the international airlines category. ATQnews Annual Awards was premiered in 1996 to recognize best performers in the aviation industry.